description.narrative:
Project objectives:

1.	To build a localised evidence-base on the varying articulations and impacts of patriarchal norms and gendered inequalities in Kyrgyzstan, Philippines, Nepal and Nigeria through the delivery of four projects;
2.	To analyse and synthesize the commonalities and differences of patriarchal gender norms and the construction of masculinities across various contexts; 
3.	To (a) develop an organisational programming framework on transforming patriarchal gender norms and violent masculinities in conflict settings and (b) drive the year two of Alert’s gender advocacy strategy from 2022 onwards.
